---
name: optimize_product_feed
description: >
  Analyze a single Merchant Center / Google Shopping product through the
  Shoptimizer service and return concrete feed-quality fixes. Use this when
  the user asks "what's wrong with this SKU's feed?", "why is this product
  disapproved?", or "how do I clean up this title/color/GTIN?". Returns the
  optimized product, a list of plugins that fired (e.g. title-word-order,
  color, identifier-exists), and a per-field diff showing exactly what changed.
---
Use for single-SKU feed quality fixes; for store-wide health use
shopping_account_health instead.
